Program: Omnibus
Title: Images of Belsen - Part Two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376m83
Last Broadcast Date: 03 July 2001
After liberation of the Nazi concentration camp of Belsen in April 1945, though the gates were open, the inmates remained in the camp and it became home to 12,000 displaced persons - some stayed there until 1950. With contributions from photographers George Rodger and Harry Oakes.